---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Services - Skief Labs" description="Data Intelligence and Sales Acceleration services for B2B companies. AI-powered outbound systems and automated data pipelines.">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-linen pt-24 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center">
        <!-- Left: Text -->
        <div>
          <h1 class="page-hero-title heading-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[3.8rem] mb-6 leading-[1.1] uppercase" style="color: #001D52;">
            Two services.<br />Both done<br />seriously.
          </h1>
          <div class="page-hero-body text-black text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
            <p>
              Skief Labs works on two specific problems for B2B companies:<br />
              getting the right data, and building the outbound systems that<br />
              turn it into pipeline. We don't offer a menu of services — just<br />
              these two, done seriously. If either problem is real for your<br />
              business, it's worth a conversation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="page-hero-cta mt-8">
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary inline-flex items-center text-xs !py-3.5 !px-6">
              Book a 30-minute discovery call
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Right: Bar chart graphic (with neon offset shadow) -->
        <div class="page-hero-image relative flex justify-center">
          <div class="w-full max-w-[420px] rounded-[10px] shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_#CFFF15] flex items-center justify-center p-8 md:p-10" style="background-color: #D9D9D9; aspect-ratio: 16/10;">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 400 220" class="w-full h-auto" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <!-- Horizontal grid lines -->
              <line x1="20" y1="40"  x2="380" y2="40"  stroke="#001D52" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.25"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="75"  x2="380" y2="75"  stroke="#001D52" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.25"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="110" x2="380" y2="110" stroke="#001D52" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.25"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="145" x2="380" y2="145" stroke="#001D52" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.25"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="180" x2="380" y2="180" stroke="#001D52" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>

              <!-- Bars (animated, ascending left to right) -->
              <rect id="svc-bar1" x="55"  y="135" width="40" height="45"  fill="#0A60FF"/>
              <rect id="svc-bar2" x="120" y="105" width="40" height="75"  fill="#0A60FF"/>
              <rect id="svc-bar3" x="185" y="75"  width="40" height="105" fill="#0A60FF"/>
              <rect id="svc-bar4" x="250" y="50"  width="40" height="130" fill="#0A60FF"/>
              <rect id="svc-bar5" x="315" y="30"  width="40" height="150" fill="#0A60FF"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <style>
          /*
            6s cycle. Each bar rises in its 1s slot then STAYS UP.
            After bar 5, all bars hold for ~1s, then loop resets all to 0.
            Slots: bar1 0-1s, bar2 1-2s, bar3 2-3s, bar4 3-4s, bar5 4-5s, pause 5-6s
          */
          @keyframes svc-bar1-build {
            0%   { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            12%  { transform: scaleY(1);    }
            100% { transform: scaleY(1);    }
          }
          @keyframes svc-bar2-build {
            0%   { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            17%  { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            29%  { transform: scaleY(1);    }
            100% { transform: scaleY(1);    }
          }
          @keyframes svc-bar3-build {
            0%   { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            33%  { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            45%  { transform: scaleY(1);    }
            100% { transform: scaleY(1);    }
          }
          @keyframes svc-bar4-build {
            0%   { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            50%  { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            62%  { transform: scaleY(1);    }
            100% { transform: scaleY(1);    }
          }
          @keyframes svc-bar5-build {
            0%   { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            67%  { transform: scaleY(0.03); }
            79%  { transform: scaleY(1);    }
            100% { transform: scaleY(1);    }
          }
          #svc-bar1 { transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: bottom; animation: svc-bar1-build 6s ease-out 1.3s infinite backwards; }
          #svc-bar2 { transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: bottom; animation: svc-bar2-build 6s ease-out 1.3s infinite backwards; }
          #svc-bar3 { transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: bottom; animation: svc-bar3-build 6s ease-out 1.3s infinite backwards; }
          #svc-bar4 { transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: bottom; animation: svc-bar4-build 6s ease-out 1.3s infinite backwards; }
          #svc-bar5 { transform-box: fill-box; transform-origin: bottom; animation: svc-bar5-build 6s ease-out 1.3s infinite backwards; }
        </style>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICE ONE: DATA INTELLIGENCE -->
  <section id="data-intelligence" class="bg-linen pt-8 pb-24 md:pt-12 md:pb-32" style="scroll-margin-top: 120px;">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16">

        <!-- LEFT: Sticky title + tagline (joins the user as they scroll) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-4">
          <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-32 page-hero-next">
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-[2.2rem] mb-4 leading-[1.25] tracking-[-0.02em]" style="color: #001D52;">
              Data Intelligence
            </h2>
            <p class="text-black text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
              The data your team needs — built, enriched,<br />and delivered automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: All subsection content, stacked -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 space-y-16 md:space-y-20">

          <!-- The Problem -->
          <div class="page-hero-next">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">The Problem</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-5 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>Most B2B teams have a data problem they've quietly learned to work around.</p>
              <ul class="space-y-3 border-l-2 pl-6" style="border-color: rgba(0,29,82,0.3);">
                <li>Lists that are months out of date before they're used.</li>
                <li>Research that pulls senior people away from higher-value work.</li>
                <li>Enrichment that's incomplete, inconsistent, or both.</li>
                <li>Decisions made on inputs no one fully trusts.</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-black font-bold">This isn't a tools problem.<br />It's a systems problem.</p>
              <p>The fix isn't another data subscription. It's a pipeline that finds, enriches, scores, and delivers the right information automatically — so the work stops requiring people.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- What We Build -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">What We Build</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:server-square-update-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Research & Scraping Pipelines</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  The data your team currently sources by hand — contacts, companies, roles, signals — collected automatically from the sources that matter for your specific use case. Continuously refreshed, not exported once and forgotten.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:magic-stick-3-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">AI-Powered Enrichment & Scoring</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Raw data isn't useful. We build enrichment logic that layers context, qualifies records, and scores outputs — so what reaches your team is clean, relevant, and ready to act on.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:cpu-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Agentic Research Workflows</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  For complex research that currently consumes senior time, we build AI agents that gather, structure, and summarize — in the exact format your team uses to make decisions.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:radar-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Signal & Trigger Identification</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Hiring activity. Funding events. Technology changes. Leadership moves. We surface the buying signals relevant to your ICP automatically, so your team acts on fresh intelligence instead of stale assumptions.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Who This Is For -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">Who This Is For</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-2xl text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-5">
              <p>Data Intelligence engagements serve teams where the quality of inputs directly determines the quality of everything downstream.</p>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 bg-neon rounded text-xs flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" style="color: #001D52;">&#10003;</span>
                  <p><span class="font-bold text-black">Marketing teams</span> using data for account targeting, segmentation, and campaign intelligence.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 bg-neon rounded text-xs flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" style="color: #001D52;">&#10003;</span>
                  <p><span class="font-bold text-black">HR and talent teams</span> using it for candidate sourcing, market mapping, and competitive research.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 bg-neon rounded text-xs flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" style="color: #001D52;">&#10003;</span>
                  <p><span class="font-bold text-black">Growth teams</span> using it to feed sales systems with reliable, continuously refreshed data.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-[10px] p-6 md:p-8 mt-6 border-l-4" style="background-color: #f9f6f0; border-left-color: #001D52;">
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed"><span class="font-bold text-black">Not a fit?</span> This is not a fit if you need a quick list or a one-time export. This is for teams with a recurring data need that has outgrown what manual effort or off-the-shelf tools can sustain — and where the cost of bad data is real and measurable.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- What Good Looks Like -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">What Good Looks Like</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-8 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>When a Data Intelligence system is working, your team stops talking about data quality.</p>
              <!-- Big stat, centered inline (no box) -->
              <div class="text-center py-6">
                <p class="font-serif text-6xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-none" style="color: #001D52;">80–90<span style="color: #CFFF15;">%</span></p>
                <p class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mt-4" style="color: #001D52;">Reduction in manual data handling</p>
              </div>
              <p>They trust the inputs. Decisions get faster. The research backlog disappears. The people who used to spend hours finding information spend that time using it instead.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- How This Engagement Works -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">How This Engagement Works</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>Every Data Intelligence engagement starts with the discovery call. From there, we scope the work properly before anything is built.</p>
              <p>We build to a fixed scope with full documentation and handoff at the end.</p>
              <p>Some clients extend into an ongoing arrangement where we continue running and refreshing the system. Others take it and run it themselves. Either way, you own it completely.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- Investment box, centered below the text -->
            <div class="flex justify-center mt-10">
              <div class="bg-navy rounded-[10px] p-8 md:p-10 w-full max-w-md">
                <p class="text-neon text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] font-semibold mb-4">Investment</p>
                <p class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl text-linen mb-4 whitespace-nowrap">System builds from <span class="text-neon">$5,000.</span></p>
                <p class="text-linen/70 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">Fixed scope. Full documentation. Handoff at the end. You own it completely.</p>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary w-full text-center block">Book a 30-minute discovery call</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICE TWO: SALES ACCELERATION -->
  <section id="sales-acceleration" class="bg-linen py-24 md:py-32" style="scroll-margin-top: 120px;">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16">

        <!-- LEFT: Sticky title + tagline (joins the user as they scroll) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-4">
          <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-32 reveal">
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-[2.2rem] mb-4 leading-[1.25] tracking-[-0.02em]" style="color: #001D52;">
              Sales Acceleration
            </h2>
            <p class="text-black text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
              More pipeline. Without more headcount.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: All subsection content, stacked -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 space-y-16 md:space-y-20">

          <!-- The Problem -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">The Problem</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-5 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>Most B2B outbound fails for a reason that has nothing to do with the product, the market, or the team.</p>
              <p>It fails because the system underneath is fragile.</p>
              <p>Manual list building. Inconsistent personalization. Follow-up that depends on someone remembering. No visibility into what's working until it's too late to fix it.</p>
              <p>The result is a lot of effort producing unpredictable results — and a team that's busy but not productive.</p>
              <p class="text-black font-bold">We fix the system. Then we run it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- What We Do -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">What We Do</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:compass-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Outbound System Design</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Before a single message is sent, we design the full targeting logic, data sources, personalization framework, and sequence architecture.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:target-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Clay-Powered Targeting</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  We use Clay as the data backbone — building dynamic lead sources, enrichment waterfalls, and scoring logic that ensures every contact your team reaches is the right one.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:chat-round-dots-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Multi-Channel Sequences</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Email and LinkedIn, working together. Touchpoints designed around actual buyer behavior and intent signals — not generic cadences copied from a playbook.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="build-card bg-linen rounded-[10px] p-7 border-2 group shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_#001D52]" style="border-color: #001D52;">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-[10px] bg-linen flex items-center justify-center text-black flex-shrink-0">
                    <iconify-icon icon="solar:rocket-2-linear" width="24" height="24"></iconify-icon>
                  </div>
                  <h4 class="text-black text-sm font-semibold whitespace-nowrap">Done-For-You Operation</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  We run the outbound. Research, enrichment, personalization, sequencing, inbox management, and continuous optimization — handled by us. Your team focuses on the conversations.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Who This Is For -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">Who This Is For</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-2xl text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-5">
              <p>Sales Acceleration is built for B2B founders, sales leaders, and growth teams who know their outbound should be working harder — and who are honest about the fact that the current approach isn't scaling.</p>
              <p>We work with a small number of Sales Acceleration clients at a time. That's not a positioning line — it's how we maintain the quality that makes the work effective.</p>
              <div class="rounded-[10px] p-6 md:p-8 mt-6 border-l-4" style="background-color: #f9f6f0; border-left-color: #001D52;">
                <p class="text-black text-sm leading-relaxed"><span class="font-bold text-black">Not a fit?</span> This is not a fit for teams looking for a short campaign or a quick blast. This is for teams who want a reliable outbound motion they can build on.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- What Good Looks Like -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">What Good Looks Like</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-8 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>When Sales Acceleration is running well, outbound stops feeling like a gamble.</p>
              <!-- Big stat, centered inline (no box) -->
              <div class="text-center py-6">
                <p class="font-serif text-6xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-none" style="color: #001D52;">3–5<span style="color: #CFFF15;">x</span></p>
                <p class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mt-4" style="color: #001D52;">More outreach capacity, same headcount</p>
              </div>
              <p>Your team has consistent conversations in the calendar. The pipeline becomes predictable. The manual research and personalization that used to take hours happens automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- How This Engagement Works -->
          <div class="reveal">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-neon rounded-full"></div>
              <h3 class="subhead-condensed text-lg font-medium tracking-wider text-black">How This Engagement Works</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-black text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              <p>Sales Acceleration begins with a pilot project — a defined scope, fixed price, and clear deliverable.</p>
              <p>The pilot covers ICP definition, data sourcing and enrichment via Clay, sequence architecture and copy, system build and launch, and first weeks of live execution.</p>
              <p>Most clients move to an ongoing monthly retainer after the pilot. There is no obligation to continue beyond the pilot.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- Investment box, centered below the text -->
            <div class="flex justify-center mt-10">
              <div class="bg-navy rounded-[10px] p-8 md:p-10 w-full max-w-md">
                <p class="text-neon text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] font-semibold mb-4">Investment</p>
                <p class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl text-linen mb-4 whitespace-nowrap">Pilot projects from <span class="text-neon">$10,000.</span></p>
